I'm saying speed is equal

00:03:41.307 --> 00:03:44.033
to magnitude of my angular velocity

00:03:44.033 --> 00:03:45.366
times my radius.

00:03:46.808 --> 00:03:51.167
So if I wanted angular velocity
as a function of speed,

00:03:51.167 --> 00:03:53.592
I could just divide both sides by r.

00:03:53.592 --> 00:03:56.167
And so I could say angular velocity

00:03:56.167 --> 00:03:58.834
is going to be equal to my speed

00:04:01.250 --> 00:04:02.083
over r.

00:04:03.267 --> 00:04:05.175
So let's think about what
happens, and let me be clear,

00:04:05.175 --> 00:04:07.983
this right over, this distance
right over here, that is r.

00:04:07.983 --> 00:04:10.467
That is r right over there.

00:04:10.467 --> 00:04:13.358
So if our velocity goes to 2v,

00:04:13.358 --> 00:04:16.342
so if this goes from v to,

00:04:16.342 --> 00:04:17.858
I'm gonna use a different color,

00:04:17.858 --> 00:04:20.025
if that goes from v to 2v,

00:04:22.792 --> 00:04:26.959
then this is gonna go from
negative v to negative 2v.

00:04:28.525 --> 00:04:31.025
And our speed is gonna go from v

00:04:31.025 --> 00:04:33.692
to just 2v, the twice the speed.

00:04:35.583 --> 00:04:37.817
And if you have twice the speed,

00:04:37.817 --> 00:04:40.275
if this goes by two,

00:04:40.275 --> 00:04:43.400
well, then the angular velocity

00:04:43.400 --> 00:04:46.775
is going to increase by a factor of two.

00:04:46.775 --> 00:04:48.633
So this is going to
increase by a factor of two,

00:04:48.633 --> 00:04:50.558
not squaring this or something else.

00:04:50.558 --> 00:04:52.900
You're just multiplying
this by one over r.

00:04:52.900 --> 00:04:54.775
You're just dividing it by r.

00:04:54.775 --> 00:04:58.250
And r is not changing,
just the speed is changing.

00:04:58.250 --> 00:05:00.175
And since omega is equal to v over r,

00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:03.200
if you double v, you're
gonna double omega.

00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:06.342
So how does the angular
velocity of the wheels change?

00:05:06.342 --> 00:05:08.025
Well, it's going to double.

00:05:08.025 --> 00:05:09.275
It will double.

